      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ validation of hemolysis index predictions",
      "description": "Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation applied to CFD hemolysis index predictions across 5 flow-speed operating points. 1000 samples drawn from input parameter distributions (viscosity, RBC fragility coefficient, shear stress exponent). 95th-percentile hemolysis index remains below clinical threshold at all operating points.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/montecarlo-hemolysis-1000samples"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-mesh-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity and discretization error assessment",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed on three mesh refinement levels (4M, 12M, 36M elements). GCI for wall shear stress QoI converges to 3.2% on the fine mesh. Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization error bound on hemolysis index.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/gci-discretization-hemolysis"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-experimental-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis comparison — FDA pump bench data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA generic centrifugal pump experimental data at 2500 and 3500 RPM across three flow rates. Mean absolute percentage error of 18.4% observed. Inherent variability in experimental hemolysis measurements assessed qualitatively by subject matter experts, accounting for donor-to-donor RBC fragility variation and sample handling artefacts; no structured probabilistic UQ node was linked for this result."
